<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Denominational_flags">Denominational flags</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Islamic_flag&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Denominational flags"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_(19).jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2819%29.jpg/220px-Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2819%29.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="165" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2819%29.jpg/330px-Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2819%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2819%29.jpg/440px-Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2819%29.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2559" data-file-height="1920" /></a><figcaption>Flags hung during the <a href="/wiki/Mourning_of_Muharram" title="Mourning of Muharram">Mourning of Muharram</a>, Iran.</figcaption></figure> 
<p>Although a flag representing Islam as a whole does not exist, some Islamic denominational branches and <a href="/wiki/Sufi" class="mw-redirect" title="Sufi">Sufi</a> brotherhoods employ flags to symbolize themselves. Among specific Islamic branches, <a href="/wiki/Nizari" class="mw-redirect" title="Nizari">Nizari</a> branch of <a href="/wiki/Ismaili" class="mw-redirect" title="Ismaili">Ismaili</a>-<a href="/wiki/Shia_Islam" title="Shia Islam">Shia Islam</a> employs an official flag made of green which represents Muhammad's standard and Ali's cloak, as well as a red stripe meaning blood and fire. The flag was ordained by the <a href="/wiki/Aga_Khan_IV" title="Aga Khan IV">Aga Khan IV</a> as a part of the new constitution in 1986. The flag is flown on the <a href="/wiki/Ismaili_Jamatkhana" class="mw-redirect" title="Ismaili Jamatkhana">Ismaili Jamatkhana</a>, a place for congregational worship for Ismaili Muslims during the festive occasions.<sup id="cite_ref-40" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-40">&#91;40&#93;</a></sup> The <a href="/wiki/Ahmadiyya" title="Ahmadiyya">Ahmadiyya</a> movement also employs an official flag (<i>Liwaa-i Ahmadiyya</i>) with black and white colors, first hoisted in 1939.<sup id="cite_ref-41" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-41">&#91;41&#93;</a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Mirza_Tahir_Ahmad" title="Mirza Tahir Ahmad">Mirza Tahir Ahmad</a>, the fourth caliph of the <a href="/wiki/Ahmadiyya_Caliphate" title="Ahmadiyya Caliphate">Ahmadiyya Caliphate</a>, explained the symbolism of the colours black and white in terms of the concept of revelation and prophethood.<sup id="cite_ref-42" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-42">&#91;42&#93;</a></sup> Muslim <a href="/wiki/African-American" class="mw-redirect" title="African-American">African-American</a> religious movement <a href="/wiki/Nation_of_Islam" title="Nation of Islam">Nation of Islam</a> deploys an official flag known as "The Flag of Islam" which symbolizes universal peace and harmony.<sup id="cite_ref-43" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-43">&#91;43&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>In Shia Muslim traditions, flags are a significant part of the rituals for the <a href="/wiki/Mourning_of_Muharram" title="Mourning of Muharram">Mourning of Muharram</a>. Mourners take round the flags or banners in the ritual known as <i>Alam Gardani</i> as a performance for the mourning ceremonies. Mourners also use flags to signal the beginning and the end of the mourning. All flags have guardians and they are passed down through generations.<sup id="cite_ref-44" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-44">&#91;44&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<ul class="gallery mw-gallery-traditional center">
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Ismaili_colors.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="The Nizārī Ismā&#39;īlī flag (1986)"><img alt="The Nizārī Ismā&#39;īlī flag (1986)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Ismaili_colors.svg/120px-Ismaili_colors.svg.png" decoding="async" width="120" height="80" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Ismaili_colors.svg/180px-Ismaili_colors.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Ismaili_colors.svg/240px-Ismaili_colors.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="400" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">The <a href="/wiki/Nizari" class="mw-redirect" title="Nizari">Nizārī</a> <a href="/wiki/Ismailism" class="mw-redirect" title="Ismailism">Ismā'īlī</a> flag (1986)</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Nation_of_Islam_flag.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="The Nation of Islam flag (1973)"><img alt="The Nation of Islam flag (1973)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Nation_of_Islam_flag.svg/120px-Nation_of_Islam_flag.svg.png" decoding="async" width="120" height="80" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Nation_of_Islam_flag.svg/180px-Nation_of_Islam_flag.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Nation_of_Islam_flag.svg/240px-Nation_of_Islam_flag.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="900" data-file-height="600" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">The <a href="/wiki/Nation_of_Islam" title="Nation of Islam">Nation of Islam</a> flag (1973)</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Khatmiyya_Order_Flag.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="The Khatmiyya tariqa flag"><img alt="The Khatmiyya tariqa flag" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/Khatmiyya_Order_Flag.svg/120px-Khatmiyya_Order_Flag.svg.png" decoding="async" width="120" height="60" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/Khatmiyya_Order_Flag.svg/180px-Khatmiyya_Order_Flag.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/Khatmiyya_Order_Flag.svg/240px-Khatmiyya_Order_Flag.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="300" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">The <a href="/wiki/Khatmiyya" title="Khatmiyya">Khatmiyya</a> tariqa flag</div>
		</li>
