<li id="cite_note-KDP-24"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-KDP_24-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20101121052922/http://kdpindia.com/Alam%20The%20Flag%20of%20The%20Mughal.html">"Alam – The Flag of the Mughals"</a>. Mumbai: Khadi Dyers &amp; Printers. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://kdpindia.com/Alam%20The%20Flag%20of%20The%20Mughal.html">the original</a> on 21 November 2010<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">26 February</span> 2010</span>. <q>primarily <a href="/wiki/Moss_green" class="mw-redirect" title="Moss green">moss green</a> and some flags were scarlet. Against a green field it displayed a rising sun, partially eclipsed by a body of a couching lion facing the hoist</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Alam+%E2%80%93+The+Flag+of+the+Mughals&amp;rft.place=Mumbai&amp;rft.pub=Khadi+Dyers+%26+Printers&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fkdpindia.com%2FAlam%2520The%2520Flag%2520of%2520The%2520Mughal.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIslamic+flag" class="Z3988"></span></span>
